      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", both in his Gospel and in Acts (Vogel, Klostermann).—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μαγείαις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": only here in N.T., not found in LXX or Apocryphal books, but used in Theophrastus and Plutarch, also in Josephus. It is found in a striking passage in St. Ignatius (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ephes.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", xix., 3) in reference to the shining forth of the star at the Incarnation, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὅθεν ἐλύετο πᾶσα μαγεία καὶ τᾶς δεσμός",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and it is also mentioned, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Didache 1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", v., 1, amongst the things comprised under “the way of death,” and so in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
